    • Method Detail

      • newNeuronAllele

        public NEATNeuronAllele newNeuronAllele(NEATGenotype genotype,
                               long synapseID)
        Create a new neuron allele for a neuron that is replacing the given synapse (see NEATNeuronAddMutator). If a previous mutation added a neuron by splitting this synapse then the gene from that neuron will be reused. When the corresponding synapse alleles are created the genes from the equivalent synapses will be reused if possible.
        Parameters:
        synapseID - The innovation ID of the synapse that is being split to add the new neuron.

      • newSynapseAllele

        public NEATSynapseAllele newSynapseAllele(NEATGenotype genotype,
                                 long sourceID,
                                 long destinationID)
        Create a new NEAT synapse allele. If there is already a NEATSynapseGene describing a synapse with the same randomly generated gene parameter values (if applicable) between the given source and destination it will be reused.
        Parameters:
        sourceID - the innovation ID of the source neuron.
        destinationID - the innovation ID of the destination neuron.
        Returns:
        the new allele.

      • synapseWouldCreateCycle

        public boolean synapseWouldCreateCycle(java.lang.Long sourceID,
                              java.lang.Long destinationID,
                              com.google.common.collect.Table<java.lang.Long,java.lang.Long,java.lang.Boolean> synapses)
        Utility method to check if adding the specified synapse would create a cycle.
        Parameters:
        sourceID - The source neuron ID of the proposed synapse.
        destinationID - The destination neuron ID of the proposed synapse.
        synapses - a table of synapses. The row keys are source neuron IDs and the column keys are destination neuron IDs (the values are a superfluous Boolean, the existence of the mapping row key/column key/value indicates the presence of the synapse).
        Returns:
        returns true iff adding the specified synapse would create a cycle.
